<sect2 id="gimp-view-soft-proof-view">
  <title>Proof Colors</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>View</primary>
    <secondary>Color Management</secondary>
    <tertiary>Proof Colors</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Color Management</primary>
    <secondary>Proof Colors</secondary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Proof Colors</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <para>
    Enabling <guimenuitem>Proof Colors</guimenuitem> allows you to interpret
    the colors of this view of your image using a soft-proofing profile that
    you can set using
    <link linkend="gimp-image-soft-proof-profile-assign">Soft-Proof Profile</link>.
  </para>

  <sect3>
    <title>Activating the Command</title>
    <para>
      You can access this command from the main menu through
      <menuchoice>
        <guimenu>View</guimenu>
        <guisubmenu>Color Management</guisubmenu>
        <guimenuitem>Proof Colors</guimenuitem>
      </menuchoice>.
    </para>
  </sect3>

</sect2>
